\section{Introduction}

\lettrine[nindent=0em,lines=3]{K}nown as an ancient country with long history,China is abundant in natural resources and places of historical interest.


In the late 19th and early 20th centuries when China was riven by internal divisions and take advantages of by the great powers, Chinese was  labeled as "sick man of Asia" by Western country.


In 1849,the rumors of gold nuggets that drew thousands of East Coast get-rich-quick hopefuls out to California during the Gold Rush.  People in China saw the opportunity to success. The
first Chinese immigrants went to the lucrative business of providing services for the miners as traders,grocers and restaurant owners.


By the mid-19th century, people in American was impressed by the cleanliness  of the Chinese restaurants. One patron recalled,' The best restaurants were kept by Chinese and the poorest and dearest by Americans. And the cheap prices also made the Chinese restaurants more attractive. Even though, the relationship between Chinese immigrants and American was not so good. With the gold sources declined, anti-Chinese sentiment grew.  In 1852, California restrict the "introduction of Chinese and other Asiatics", and it culminated in 1882 with the passage of the Chinese Exclusion Act, which banned all Chinese laborers from entering the United States. The act would not be repealed until 1943.


Good food was still good. The turn of the 20th century saw the emergence of Chop Suey joints as hip and affordable places for young urbanities to spend a night out.


Recently,with more than 41,000 Chinese restaurants in America - 3 times the number of McDonaldâ€™s restaurants - Chinese food is one of the most accepted and misunderstood cuisines in the United States. However, Chinese food in American is not the same as we have in China, it was changed to suit the American's appetite. So there are a lot between the Chinese-American food and traditional Chinese food.


Chinese pop culture was deeply influenced by the American culture, like music and internet. With the development of economy of Chinese, American started to learned from China,like twitter and Weibo.



Catering Culture\& POP CULTURE

wuxia is not popular in American




